<h2>Breadcrumbs</h2>
<h3 class="subheader">See <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/components/breadcrumbs.html">Foundation - Breadcrumbs</a></h3>

<hr>

<h3>Example</h3>

<div class="row">
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h4>Template</h4>
    <pre><code>\{{f-breadcrumbs}}</code></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h4>Rendered Component</h4>
    {{f-breadcrumbs}}
  </div>
</div>

<hr>

<h3>Usage</h3>

<p>Breadcrumbs are mostly automatic; they're based on the application's router and controllers. You should add a property of <code>breadCrumbName</code> to any controllers you want included in a breadcrumb component. For this app, the route <em>/components</em> has a <code>breadCrumbName</code> of "Component Demos", and the current page route of <em>/components/breadcrumbs</em> has a <code>breadCrumbName</code> of "Breadcrumbs Demo".</p>
